                                <p><b>2. Take the&nbsp;</b><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size:11pt;line-height:107%;font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;"><b>ECBA™</b></span><b>&nbsp;certification exam&nbsp;</b><br></p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Login to the <a href="https://my.iiba.org/portal/s/login/?_ga=2.205554384.2143567188.1611302465-778211366.1611302465" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">IIBA portal</a> with your credentials (received from IIBA via email).&nbsp;</li>
                                    <li>In the IIBA portal, go to&nbsp;<i>Certification</i>&nbsp;&gt;&nbsp;<i>My Certifications.&nbsp;</i>Click on&nbsp;<i>Schedule</i>&nbsp;and then click on the&nbsp;<i>Pass Exam</i>&nbsp;button.&nbsp;</li>
                                    <li>You’ll be taken to the PSI exam scheduling page, where you can schedule the ECBA exam.&nbsp;</li>
                                    <li>Take the ECBA test and answer 50 MCQs in 60 minutes.&nbsp;<br></li>
                                </ul>
                                <p><b>3. Become&nbsp;an ECBA certified Business Analysis professional</b></p>
                                <p>Download the Entry Certificate in Business Analysis Course (ECBA) certificate and validate your expertise as a certified BA professional.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<br></p>
