                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-1-1">1. What is ECBA?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-1-1" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-1">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>ECBA or the Entry Certificate in Business Analysis (ECBA) is the certification offered by IIBA. The ECBA certification exam checks your proficiency in the knowledge and understanding of the field of business analysis. Therefore, this exam recognizes the entry-level individuals in the business analysis domain.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-1-2">2. What can I expect to accomplish after completing the ECBA™ course?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-1-2" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-1">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>The Entry Certificate in Business Analysis (ECBA) certificate and validate your expertise as a certified BA professional.&nbsp; Our ECBA course has been thoughtfully designed to make you a skilled Business Analysis. At the end of the course, you’ll be able to:&nbsp;</p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>Organize and coordinate business analysis efforts.&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Prepare and conduct elicitation activities and confirm the results.&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Manage and maintain requirements and design information from inception to retirement.&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Identify and address business needs and align change strategy within the enterprise.&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Organize, specify, and model requirements and designs.&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Validate and verify information, identify solution options, estimate and realize the potential value.&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Assess the performance of and value delivered by a solution.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-1-3">3. Is the ECBA certification worth it? Does ECBA help get a job?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-1-3" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-1">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>ECBA is an exam that helps entry-level business analysts validate their business analysis skills. The business analyst marketplace can be extremely competitive. Those who are just entering the industry as an analyst may not have the advantages of other candidates with a high-powered degree or a consultancy background. The ECBA certification can be a good way to show their ambitions and determination in the field.&nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-1-4">4. What practical skills can I expect to have after completing the ECBA™ course?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-1-4" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-1">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>Our ECBA training online program aims to equip you with all the skills to be an effective Business Analysis. By the end of this ECBA training course, you will have developed the following practical skills:&nbsp;</p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>Business Analysis Planning&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Business Analysis Monitoring&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Business Analysis Approach&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Stakeholder Engagement Approach&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Business Analysis Governance&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Business Analysis Information Management&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Business Analysis Performance Improvements&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Elicitation – Prepare and Conduct&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Confirming Elicitation Results&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Communicating Business Analysis Information&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Stakeholder Collaboration Management&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Requirements - Trace, Maintain, Prioritize and Approve&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Requirements Change Assessment&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Current State Analysis&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Define Future State&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Risk Assessment&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Change Strategy Development&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Requirements – Specify, Model, Verify and Validate&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Define Requirements Architecture and Design Options&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Analyse Potential Value and Recommend Solution&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Measure Solution Performance&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Analyse Performance measures&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Assess Solution and Enterprise Limitations&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Recommend Actions to Increase Value&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
                                            </ul>
                                            <p>KnowledgeHut is known for its top trainers and a comprehensive curriculum, making it one of the best ECBA online courses. These offerings and immersive learning will help you master the skills needed to be a sought-after Business Analyst.&nbsp;</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-1-5">5. How does an ECBA™ certification training help me? </a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-1-5" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-1">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>The ECBA training course provides you a host of benefits, including:&nbsp;</p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>Demonstrable fundamental knowledge and professional competence in Business Analysis.&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Marketability, employability, and higher earning potential.&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Successful path to leadership.&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Recognizing your expertise in multiple business domains.&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Enhancing your ability to tackle more complex projects, work with stakeholders to define and manage their business requirements.&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Empowers you to drive business processes, lead the BA effort, and identify opportunities to achieve better business results.&nbsp;</li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-1-6">6. Is the ECBA™ course only for software developers? </a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-1-6" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-1">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>Not at all. The ECBA course is for anyone who aspires career growth in business analysis, including: IT professionals&nbsp;</p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>Project managers&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Banking and finance professionals&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Marketing managers&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Sales professionals&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Data Analytics Beginners&nbsp;</li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-1-7">7. What are the software and system requirements?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-1-7" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-1">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>Software Requirements &nbsp;</p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>Internet browser &nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>System Requirements &nbsp;</li>
                                            </ul>
                                            <p>Windows or equivalent environment with Internet browser and high-speed Internet connectivity. </p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-1-8">8. What are the prerequisites for this course? </a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-1-8" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-1">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <div>
                                                <div>Although there are no prerequisites for this course, prior experience in business analysis and specialized areas are highly recommended. </div>
                                                <div><br></div>
                                                <div>To become eligible for the Entry Certificate in Business Analysis (ECBA) certification applicants must complete at least 21 hours of Professional Development (PD) training in the last 4 years. This can include:&nbsp;</div>
                                                <div><br></div>
                                            </div>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>Classroom courses (IIBA® Education Endorsed Provider courses, other training providers courses)&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Chapter events (presentations, workshops, conference days)&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Chapter study groups&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Conferences (keynotes, track sessions, tutorials, workshops)&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Self-directed learning (reading/studying the BABOK® Guide v3, archived webinars)&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Online courses (IIBA® Education Endorsed Provider courses, other training providers courses, live webinars) &nbsp;</li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-1-9">9. What next after ECBA™? </a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-1-9" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-1">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>Once you have completed the Entry Certificate in Business Analysis training, you can further enhance your Business Analysis skills by pursuing the following credentials &nbsp;</p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>CBAP®&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>PMI-PBA®&nbsp;</li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="cert-and-exam-section" id="ecba-certificationprocess-2">
                            <h3>ECBA Certification Process</h3>
                            <div class="course-cert-faq-content accordion-cards custom-cards" id="faq-accordion-2">
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-1">1. Who provides the ECBA certificate?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-1" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>The ECBA certificate is offered by the International Institute of Business Analysis (IIBA®), the global leader in business analysis competency guidelines. IIBA® is a world-renowned body dedicated to helping professionals, leaders and organizations gain an in-depth understanding of real-world business analysis situations. &nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-2">2. Can I get certified without taking the course?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-2" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>You can study on your own and take the examination directly from IIBA® without attending an ECBA training course. However, this may prove to be very challenging. To be abreast of the latest guidelines from IIBA® and the ECBA certification requirements, it is highly recommended that you get trained for the ECBA certification by an IIBA-registered Endorsed Education Provider™ (EEP™) like KnowledgeHut. You’ll benefit from comprehensive ECBA preparation support and a 100% money-back guarantee. <br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-3">3. What is the process to get the Entry Certificate in Business Analysis certification?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-3" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>Here are the steps to get ECBA certified:&nbsp;</p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>Fulfill the eligibility requirements for ECBA certification.&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Register for KnowledgeHut’s ECBA course and attend the 21-Hours training.&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Login to the IIBA portal with your IIBA credentials (received via mail).&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Pay ECBA Application Fee&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Enter BA Development Log Hours&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Pay the ECBA exam fee.&nbsp;<br></li>
                                                <li>Take the ECBA test and answer 50 MCQs in 60 minutes.&nbsp;<br></li>
                                                <li>Download the ECBA certificate and lead BA initiatives! &nbsp;</li>
                                            </ul>
                                            <p>Your ECBA certification will be valid for life. &nbsp;</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-4">4. Where can I get detailed information about the ECBA exam and certification?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-4" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>You will get detailed information about applying for the ECBA exam in IIBA’s <a href="https://www.iiba.org/globalassets/certification/files/core-ba-certification-handbook.pdf" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Core BA Certification Handbook</a>. The handbook provides information on all testing modalities, policies, and procedures for obtaining and maintaining the ECBA certification. You will find tips and important information on the certification process. &nbsp;<span style="color:#000;font-family:Calibri,Calibri_EmbeddedFont,Calibri_MSFontService,sans-serif;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-5">5. Do I need to earn all the 21 contact hours from one ECBA course?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-5" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>You do not need to earn all 21 contact hours from one ECBA course. However, it is more structured to acquire all the ECBA knowledge from a single course that focuses on the latest <i>BABOK® Guide </i>v3 framework. &nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-6">6. Should I have completed the 21 ECBA contact hours before submitting ECBA application?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-6" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>Yes, you should have completed the 21 ECBA contact hours before submitting your ECBA application. You would need to enter the course details together with the date of completion on the application form before submitting. &nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-7">7. What’s the BABOK® Guide v3 about? What’s the latest edition?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-7" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>The <i><a href="https://www.iiba.org/career-resources/a-business-analysis-professionals-foundation-for-success/babok/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">BABOK® Guide</a>&nbsp;</i> refers to <i>A Guide to the Business Analysis Body of Knowledge® (BABOK® Guide)</i>, developed via a rigorous consensus-driven standards process and incorporates the collective wisdom and experience of experts in the BA field from around the world. The latest edition is v3.0.<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-8">8. How important is the BABOK® Guide v3 to prepare for the ECBA Exam?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-8" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>The<i><a href="https://www.iiba.org/career-resources/a-business-analysis-professionals-foundation-for-success/babok/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"> BABOK® Guide</a></i> v3 is a great resource and an extremely useful one to prepare for the ECBA exam. It defines the skills and knowledge required by business analysis professionals covering the six knowledge areas and the business analysis competency model. It extends its scope beyond business analysis in projects to address agile development, business process management, business intelligence, and business architecture.&nbsp;</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-9">9. Do you provide a course completion certificate?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-9" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>Yes, you will receive a course completion certificate from KnowledgeHut on successfully completing the course.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-10">10. How long does it take to get an ECBA™ certification?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-10" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>The time you require depends on your effort and capability as well as your experience and qualifications. You would need to attend 21 Hours of ECBA training under a Certified BA Trainer following which you will be required to take an exam to demonstrate your knowledge of Business Analysis to get certified. Once you pass the exam, you are declared ECBA certified and can instantly download your certificate. &nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-11">11. Will my certificate say ‘Virtual’ if I take the certification online?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-11" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>No, your certificate will not mention the course was held online. It will look the same as the in-person certificates. &nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-12">12. How can the ECBA certification status be verified?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-12" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>The ECBA certification status can be verified via IIBA’s <a href="https://directory.credential.net/internationalinstituteofbusinessanalysis" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Certification Registry</a>. However, inclusion in the registry is voluntary, so not all certification holders may be listed. &nbsp;</p>
                                            <p>To verify a certification holder's status, enter an individual's last name/surname in the search field and a list of matches will be displayed. &nbsp;</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-13">13. Do I have to renew ECBA certification?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-13" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>No, you do not have to renew ECBA certification since, it is valid for life.&nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-14">14. What is the cost of ECBA certification?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-14" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>The ECBA price is not a big constraint when it comes to the ECBA certification. In fact, the <b>ECBA certification cost</b> depends on your geographical location. There is a misconception that a student has to burn a big hole in their pocket when it comes to ECBA price, but you’ll be happy to know that the exam application fees are US$60 and the exam fees can range from US$110 - US$195, depending on whether you are a member or a non-member of IIBA.&nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-15">15. What is the most recognized business analyst certification?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-15" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>Search results say that CBAP is the best certification.<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="cert-and-exam-section" id="pd-hours-pdus-and-cdus-3">
                            <h3>PD hours, PDUs and CDUs</h3>
                            <div class="course-cert-faq-content accordion-cards custom-cards" id="faq-accordion-3">
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-3-1">1. What are PD hours?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-3-1" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-3">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content"> <b>PD hours</b> are Professional Development hours issued by International Institute of Business Analysis (IIBA)®. They are earned by completing educational training or learning opportunities, which serve to validate your participation and continued proficiency in the principles and practices of Business Analysis in line with the <i>BABOK® Guide</i>. 1 hour of Professional Development = 1 Contact Hour.&nbsp; </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-3-2">2. What are CDUs?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-3-2" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-3">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p><b>CDUs</b> are Continuing Development Units needed for maintaining one’s IIBA certification. They can be earned by participating in formal training opportunities, like certified courses from any accreditation body, and other forms of learning opportunities like webinars, self-study courses, etc.&nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-3-3">3. What are PDUs?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-3-3" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-3">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p><b>PDUs</b> are Professional Development Units issued by the Project Management Institute, Inc® (PMI®). They can be earned by completing educational training or learning opportunities, which serve to validate your participation and continued proficiency in the principles and practices of project management. &nbsp;</p>
                                            <p>‘PDU’ refers to measuring units used to quantify your professional development as part of the PMI’s Continuing Certification Requirements (CCR) program. 1 PDU = 1 hour of learning/activity. </p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-3-4">4. Where are PDUs applicable?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-3-4" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-3">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>PDUs recognize your dedication to the project management world through the award of credits for every educational effort you make throughout your career. PDUs are offered by the PMI and requires you to earn a specific number of PDUs per three-year certification cycle. &nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-3-5">5. Where are PD hours applicable?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-3-5" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-3">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>PDs recognize your dedication to the project management world through the award of credits for every educational effort you make throughout your career. PDs are offered by the IIBA and requires you to earn a specific number of PDUs per three-year certification cycle.&nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-3-6">6. How many PDUs and CDUs will I be eligible for? </a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-3-6" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-3">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>You will be eligible for 21 PDUs and 21 CDUs on course completion. &nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-3-7">7. How many PD hours will I be eligible for?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-3-7" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-3">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>You will be eligible for 21 PD hours on course completion. &nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-3-8">8. How many CDUs will I be eligible for?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-3-8" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-3">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>You will be eligible for 21 CDUs on course completion. &nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-3-9">9. How do I earn PD hours?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-3-9" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-3">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>You can earn PD hours by attending training programs offered by an Endorsed Education Provider™ (EEP™) of IIBA or by eligible organizations/universities. Whenever you attend an IIBA congress, webinar, conference, or any other event or indulge in self-directed learning, you can earn PDs. &nbsp;</p>
                                            <p>For a training program or course to qualify towards IIBA’s Professional Development requirement, it must meet the following criteria:&nbsp;</p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>It must be moderated/facilitated similar to a formal course (i.e., there must be a moderator for the session or a facilitator/instructor who leads the group/individual through the material).&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>There must be a measurable learning objective (or set of objectives), and those must be directly applicable to the role of the business analyst (i.e., in terms of either changing behaviour or improving skills).&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>It cannot simply be a presentation on a specific topic.&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>There must be an opportunity for students to interact with the material (e.g., be able to ask questions, make the learning meaningful).&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>An opportunity to practice the task or objective being presented and, be assessed by the facilitator/moderator.&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>The subject matter must be directly aligned with the <i>BABOK® Guide</i>.&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>To qualify, courses must also be completed by the application submitted date and have a start date within the last four years from the application submitted date.&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>KnowledgeHut’s ECBA certification course automatically qualifies towards the professional development requirement of IIBA as KnowledgeHut is an EEP of IIBA.&nbsp;</li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-3-10">10. How do I earn PDUs? </a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-3-10" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-3">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>You can earn PDUs by attending training programs offered by PMI Authorized Training Partners or by organizations or universities. Whenever you attend a PMI congress, webinar, conference, or any other event or indulge in self-directed learning, you can earn PDUs. &nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-3-11">11. How do I earn CDUs?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-3-11" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-3">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>The requirements for some categories of CDUs are more lenient. Self-study courses, webinars, professional development meetings, and other less formal training opportunities to learn about business analysis can all qualify for CDUs. As is the case with PDUs, an offering can qualify for CDUs even if it’s not pre-endorsed by IIBA as long as the opportunity meets the requirements of the CDU category you list it under. For more information, please refer the following recertification handbooks:&nbsp;</p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li><a href="https://www.iiba.org/globalassets/certification/recertification/files/ccba-and-cbap-recertification-handbook.pdf" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">CBAP Recertification Handbook</a>.&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li><a href="https://www.iiba.org/link/fcab75bfb7354420aace061f1a2441e7.aspx" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">AAC Recertification Handbook</a>&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li><a href="https://www.iiba.org/link/d56e69f1789444bf85ce0fb82704bde5.aspx" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">CBDA Recertification Handbook</a></li>
                                            </ul>
                                            <ul class="BulletListStyle1 SCXW138839178 BCX0" role="list" style="margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding:0px;user-select:text;-webkit-user-drag:none;-webkit-tap-highlight-color:transparent;overflow:visible;cursor:text;font-family:verdana;color:#000;font-size:14.6667px;">
                                                <li data-leveltext="" data-font="Symbol" data-listid="55" aria-setsize="-1" data-aria-posinset="3" role="listitem" data-aria-level="1" class="OutlineElement Ltr SCXW138839178 BCX0" style="margin:0px 0px 0px 24px;padding:0px;user-select:text;-webkit-user-drag:none;-webkit-tap-highlight-color:transparent;overflow:visible;cursor:text;clear:both;position:relative;direction:ltr;display:block;font-size:11pt;font-family:Calibri,Calibri_MSFontService,sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;"></li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-3-12">12. What are the qualifying activity categories for CDUs?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-3-12" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-3">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>The qualifying activity categories for CDUs are as follows:&nbsp;</p>
                                            <table class="table table-bordered">
                                                <tbody>
